2 bard.  Already have the horn.  White scale is the last thing I need for the epic.   Resists are off the charts and I may have some extra resist gear to loan out.<br><br>I read the debate over the scale in the last thread.  /boggle  Sorry Jex to misplace my contention on a scheduling thread but it has bearing here.  This is not in response to Jex or the stated loot policy but in reply to the authors asserting that intel casters should roll on the scale in a debate in a prior Vox thread.<br><br>Am I the only one who believes in the highest use of an item?  Do people not understand that attaining this god forsaken scale is the sole, only, lone, singular way for bards to get their epics whereas there are a ton of ways for an intel caster to get intel to 200 with a load of mana/hps and resists.  It's not that hard. Don't GEBs that drop from the Efreeti give the same amount of intel/wis?  5k or camped with one group or three good players. What's the book of obulous add 8 int and 8 wis?  Those go for a whopping 2k these days and drop randomly in Sebilis.  What about the runed cowl - isn't that around 9 to int?  You gotta be uber to buy one of those for 1k or camp/solo the treacherous zone of Lower Guk.  I'll bet the sage spawns more than once a week and doesn't take 30 people to kill ala Vox.   I'm sure you can think of 100 other similiar items. <br><br>I played a necro to 60 and he didn't have any fancy eyepatch or white dragon scale cloak.  Hell he didn't even have a planar quality robe and I could still get his intel to 235 if I wanted to (dangling prepostion).  It's not that hard. Scaling down the intel to 200 and getting his resists up was not a problem either.  I understand the fact that you want to better your character.  I also understand, unlike the bard epic, that this item is not the only way to do that nor does it justify the potential cost to those you are raiding with.  It also doesn't justify two bites at the apple for casters.  First, you will want to roll on the patch.  If you lose then you'll want to roll on the scale.  Why not just roll on the RBB too?  I hear that the haste helps the casters with their interrupt rates and plus it would look &quot;l33t&quot; in your inventory.  Then the warriors can roll for the eyepatch.  After all they could use the intel to help their skills go up faster.  The bards (this one at least) aren't complaining about rolling on the RBB/COF because we realize that it's not the highest use.  We would be slighting the real tanks.  The premise here is the same reason you don't see wizards rolling to beat necros on Inny's eye.<br><br>Solution:  The proponents for the scale going to int casters are preaching that they just want it for the cloak.  Tell ya what, if the intel casters want the scale only for the cloak and not to win it and resell it at a jacked rate consequently screwing your fellow raid mates, then you will gladly allow the bards present to random to see who has the right to trade you a white dragonscale cloak for the scale.  I've seen a bunch of those White Dragonscale Cloaks for sale quite frenquently as of late.  There is a post on the item bazaar right now - Ruler2 is selling one for 32k.  You get your cloak and we get the scale.  If your only motivation is the cloak then you should have absolutely no problems with this proposition.  If a cloak is unavailable, I for one would compensate you so you could find other highly valuable intel items that would equally complement your character as much as the cloak would.<br><br>I don't really like my proposed solution but I can't think of a better alternative.  It's lame for bards to have to buy an item that is irreplacable to their class and would be of absolute highest use but I can't think of an alternative that will please the gallery.  Ideas?<br><br>If you need to categorize the above as a flame to fulfill an incessant need to label and box things then there will be no stopping you.  However, unlike typical bitch